## ðŸš€ Quick Start

### Prerequisites
```bash
conda create -n cyber-ml python=3.10
conda activate cyber-ml
pip install -r requirements-ml.txt
```

### Training Example
```bash
python ml/training/train_model.py \
  --data ml/datasets/processed/v1.parquet \
  --config ml/configs/production.yml \
  --output-dir ml/models/experimental/
```
## ðŸ”§ Key Components
### Data Processing
```python
from ml.preprocessing import CyberDataProcessor

processor = CyberDataProcessor()
df_clean = processor.fit_transform(raw_data)
```

### Model Training
```python
from ml.training import ModelTrainer

trainer = ModelTrainer()
best_model = trainer.train(
    data_path="ml/datasets/processed/train.parquet",
    model_type="xgboost"
)
```
## ðŸ“Š Data Schema


Field       |	Type	  | Description	           |  Example
---------------------------------------------------------------
timestamp   |	datetime  |	Event timestamp (UTC)  | 2023-08-01 14:30:00
src_ip      |	string	  | Hashed source IP       | (SHA-256)	ip_5f3a...
protocol    |	category  |	tcp, udp, or icmp	   | tcp
payload_len |	int	Packet| payload length in bytes| 1024
is_malicious|	bool	  | Ground truth label	   | True


